<font color="#FF0000">MY HELL</font><br>
<tt>Wed Sep 17 21:34:02 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Never knew what PSTD was and am not sure now.<br>
No emotion ever.  No crying, no remorse, no empathy, no fear, nothing.  All responses clinically evaluated and manufactured to what I perceived as the norm.  Overboard on the nice guy routine to prevent anyone knowing I just didn't care.<br><br>
No intermediate position.  To lose it was weakness and fear that their would be no return.  Countless times there is rage, burning killing rage, capped just below the surface.<br><br>
You learn to avoid situations which might take you over the top.  You learn to have what people call a slow fuse.  All a facade.<br><br>
You become a work fanatic.  Class AAAA.  You need a crisis to heighten the awareness.  If there isn't a conflict you create one.  If there isn't enough work to stress you out you seek other peoples problems.<br><br>
Everything you do is stress at the pain level.  Exercise, bike riding, yard work, life in general.<br><br>
You use this stress, pain, to occupy the mind at the 100% level.  It calms the soul to not be able to think.  It helps to not find your self thinking about lady death.  Found my self at times not wanting to pull out of a dive.  Swam out to sea once just to check the distance.  Bad judgement doesn't make you guilty.  Damn guys in a boat always want to give you a ride.  My wife used to watch in vain as I would jog in a night snow storm or ride a dirt bike with insane abandon.<br><br>
I don't know what this means.  Didn't care until now.  I am not even sure VN had anything to do with.<br><br>
I am filled with controlled rage now.  I don't what it is, but I know it is relentless, but the strange thing is the peace you find when you are 100% consumed.<br><br>
No visions, flashbacks, or sounds.  Sleep, not much.<br><br>
My symtoms of what ever it is.<br><br>
SW<br>

